headline: What Analysts Think Is Shifting The Story For Conagra Brands (CAG) Versus Peers
summary: Conagra Brands has just seen a small lift in its fair value estimate, with the price target moving from US$18.81 to US$19.05 as analysts refresh their views after the 2026 CAGNY conference. This tweak ties back to updated revenue growth assumptions of 44.20% in the models and a slightly lower discount rate of 7.05%, reflecting how recent guidance and free cash flow commentary are filtering into valuations. Stay tuned to see how you can track these kinds of narrative shifts and target changes...
